title: Membership of Review Committee on Regulation of Pharmaceutical Products announced
content_text:
p>
The Government today (March 24) announced the membership and terms of 
reference of the Review Committee on Regulation of Pharmaceutical Products 
in Hong Kong. In the light of the recent drug incidents, the Secretary for Food and Health 
last Thursday (March 19) announced the setting up of a review committee to 
undertake a comprehensive review of the existing regulatory regime for the 
regulation and control of pharmaceutical products. The review committee will be chaired by the Permanent Secretary for Food and 
Health (Health), Ms Sandra Lee, and comprises members from the

Health (Health), Ms Sandra Lee, and comprises members from the 
pharmaceutical sector, medical profession, academia, patient groups and 
consumer representatives, among others. The review committee will conduct a comprehensive review on all the relevant 
issues including safety and quality assurance of drugs, standard and 
practices of the pharmaceutical industry, and whether there is a need for 
legislative amendments. To support the work of the review committee, the Director of Health has set 
up a task force to comprehensively review the existing control of the drug

up a task force to comprehensively review the existing control of the drug 
supply chain, including manufacturers, importers, wholesalers and retailers, 
as well as the control of drugs. An Expert Group on Microbiological Hazards on Drug Manufacturing will also 
make proposals to the task force. Their recommendations will be put to the 
review committee for deliberation. The Department of Health will enlist the 
assistance of a reputable overseas authority to assist and advise on the 
work of the task force.  The first meeting of the review committee will be held in early April. It is

expected that the review will be completed in six to nine months' time. The following is the membership of the review committee: Chairman:
Permanent Secretary for Food and Health (Health), Ms Sandra Lee Vice Chairman:
Director of Health, Dr Lam Ping-yan Non-Official members:
